-- Kenya's Centum Investment pretax profit up 24 pct in year to March
-- By Duncan Miriri
-- Tue Jun 10, 2014 01:57AM EDT
-- None



NAIROBI, June 10 (Reuters) - Kenya's Centum Investment <ICDC.NR> increased its pretax profit in the year to March by 24 percent to 4.01 billion shillings ($45.83 million) over the previous 12 months, the firm said on Tuesday.

The company which invests in private equity, listed firms and real estate said dividend income climbed 53 percent in the period.